  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AL-02 sensitivity gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across all five flow-speed operating points; a screening sensitivity study was conducted during model development and informally documented in the project technical report, but no structured sensitivity analysis record is linked to this package. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; required and achieved levels reflect MRL 5 demands. Decision: Accepted based on the totality of evidence, with the understanding that UQ bounds are considered sufficient for regulatory submission.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "hasUncertaintyQuantification": true,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req",
